Rexon Inc said it filed aregistration statement with the Securities and ExchangeCommission covering the primary sale of 1.25 mln common sharesthrough an underwriting group managed by Hambrecht and Quist.    Rexon, a maker of tape drives, subsystems andcomputer-related products, said it plans to use proceeds fromthe sale for working capital and for capital expenditures,primarily related to the company's tape drive products. Reuter&#3;